{
  "texts": [
    "These surveys reviewed a series of work on artistic stylization [76],appearance editing [124], text-to-image transitions [165], and the newfound applications of AI across multiple data modalities [173].",
    "Methodologically, they span neural style transfer [67], GAN inversion [153] to attention mechanisms [52] and diffusion models [23]-each contributing to the state of the art in their own right.",
    "From an application perspective, they explore the transformative integration of AIGC across various domains, and while remarkable, they also highlight challenges that call for further development and ethical consideration [93,155].",
    "Meanwhile, surveys with an artistic focus unravel the interplay between arts and humanities within the AIGC era, probing into the processing and understanding of art through advanced computational methods [7,18,89], the generative potential of AI in creating novel art forms [36,168], and the applicability of its integration in enhancing educational and therapeutic experiences attention mechanisms, personalization, control, quality, modularity, multi-tasking, and efficiency [15,75,119].",
    "The synthesis of these trends reflects a dynamic evolution in diffusion-based generative models, marking a transformative era in visual art creation.The frontiers of diffusion-based visual art creation are seen through the lens of technical evolution and human-AI collaboration."
  ]
}